'''Giorgian Daniel de Arrascaeta Benedetti''' (born 1 June 1994) is a Uruguayan professional [[Football player|footballer]] who plays as an [[Midfielder|attacking midfielder]]  for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

Arrascaeta played for [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay U20]] and has been a member of the senior team since 2014. He represented the nation at the [[Copa América]] in [[2015 Copa América|2015]], [[2019 Copa América|2019]], [[2021 Copa América|2021]] and [[2024 Copa América|2024]], as well as the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]].

==Club career==
===Defensor Sporting===
Arrascaeta debuted for [[Defensor Sporting]] in the [[Uruguayan Primera División]] in October 2012, four months after his 18th birthday.<ref name=gda>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2014/10/27/futbol/futbol_internacional/resto_de_america/1414425571.html|title=De Arrascaeta interesa al Milan|date=27 October 2014|work=Marca|archive-date=3 September 2022|access-date=13 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220903101316/https://www.marca.com/2014/10/27/futbol/futbol_internacional/resto_de_america/1414425571.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He was a member of the team as it won the [[2012–13 Uruguayan Primera División season#Championship playoff|2013 Clausura]] championship, and played in the [[2012–13 Uruguayan Primera División season#Championship playoff|Championship play-off]], a 3–1 loss to [[Peñarol]].<ref name=gda/>

===Cruzeiro===
Arrascaeta's performances for Defensor in its run to the semi-finals of the [[2014 Copa Libertadores]] attracted the Brazilian champions [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]]. On 17 January 2015 Cruzeiro secured de Arrascaeta signing by agreeing to pay [[Euro|€]]4 million (R$12 million) to acquire 50% of his economic rights.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 January 2015 |title=Cruzeiro vence disputa com o Inter e acerta a contratação de Arrascaeta |trans-title=Cruzeiro wins the dispute with Inter and finalizes the signing of Arrascaeta. |url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/cruzeiro/noticia/2015/01/cruzeiro-vence-disputa-com-o-inter-e-confirma-contratacao-de-arrascaeta.html |access-date=22 April 2021 |website=Globoesporte.com |language=pt-BR |archive-date=9 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230609064303/https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/cruzeiro/noticia/2015/01/cruzeiro-vence-disputa-com-o-inter-e-confirma-contratacao-de-arrascaeta.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

In Cruzeiro, Arrascaeta formed a midfield strong, which became known as "La Banda", along with [[Lucas Romero]] and [[Ariel Cabral]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/world-match-centre/news/newsid/251/285/4/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205062034/http://www.fifa.com/world-match-centre/news/newsid/251/285/4/|url-status=dead|archive-date=5 February 2015|title=Eto'o, Odegaard moves catch the eye|date=30 January 2015|work=FIFA}}</ref> This trio, along with fellow stars [[Thiago Neves]] and [[Robinho (footballer, born November 1987)|Robinho]] helped Cruzeiro to conquer the [[2017 Copa do Brasil]],the [[2018 Campeonato Mineiro]], and [[2018 Copa do Brasil]], with Arrascaeta scoring decisive goals in all three finals.{{citation needed|date=March 2026}}

On 4 February 2018 Cruzeiro won 1–0 against [[América Futebol Clube (MG)|América Mineiro]] at [[Mineirão]], in a [[2018 Campeonato Mineiro]] match.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 February 2018 |title=Com golaço de Arrascaeta, Cruzeiro vence América-MG e se isola na liderança do Mineiro |trans-title=With a stunning goal from Arrascaeta, Cruzeiro defeats América-MG and takes the lead in the Mineiro championship. |url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/mg/futebol/campeonato-mineiro/jogo/04-02-2018/cruzeiro-america-mg/ |access-date=22 April 2021 |website=Globoesporte.com |language=pt-BR |archive-date=28 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428105334/http://globoesporte.globo.com/mg/futebol/campeonato-mineiro/jogo/04-02-2018/cruzeiro-america-mg/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Arrascaeta scored the only goal of the match with a [[Volley (association football)|volley kick]], later that year he received his first nomination to the [[FIFA Puskás Award]] for that goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/puskas-award/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103091359/http://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/puskas-award/|url-status=dead|archive-date=3 November 2016|title=FIFA Puskás Award 2018 Nominees|work=FIFA.com|access-date=3 September 2018}}</ref>

===Flamengo===
[[File:Arrascaeta Libertadores 2021.jpg|thumb|left|160px|Giorgian de Arrascaeta playing for [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] in the [[2021 Copa Libertadores final]].]]

During [[2019 in Brazilian football|2019]] preseason [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] began to show interest in de Arrascaeta. On 3 January 2019, he didn't show up on training sessions after the summer break trying to force his exit from Cruzeiro.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arrascaeta, Cruzeiro, e Flamengo: veja todos os detalhes da novela. |trans-title=Arrascaeta, Cruzeiro, and Flamengo: see all the details of the saga. |url=http://www.espn.com.br/futebol/artigo/_/id/5151952/arrascaeta-cruzeiro-e-flamengo-veja-todos-os-detalhes-da-novela |access-date=10 January 2019 |publisher=[[ESPN]] Brazil}}</ref> Claiming to receive thousands of insults, on 7 January 2019, Cruzeiro's and Flamengo's representatives went to Uruguay to resolve the problem: on 8 January, the transfer was completed for a record [[Euro|€]]15million, or [[Brazilian real|R$]]63 million, the biggest transfer in Brazilian football history.<ref>{{cite news |title=Fla fecha com Arrascaeta em maior compra da história do futebol brasileiro |trans-title=Fla completes deal with Arrascaeta in the biggest transfer in the history of Brazilian football. |url=https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2019/01/08/fla-fecha-com-arrascaeta-em-maior-compra-da-historia-do-futebol-brasileiro.htm |access-date=10 January 2019 |publisher=Esporte UOL}}</ref> On 12 January he was announced as a new player, becoming Flamengo's biggest transfer fee paid at that time, signing a five-year deal.

Against [[Goiás Esporte Clube|Goiás]] in the second match under [[Jorge Jesus]] management de Arrascaeta scored a hat trick, with all of his goals scored in the first half, in the 6–1 win at [[Maracanã Stadium]] on 14 July 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 July 2019 |title=Com show de Arrascaeta e estreia de Rafinha, Flamengo goleia por 6 a 1 o Goiás no Maracanã |trans-title=With a performance from Arrascaeta and Rafinha's debut, Flamengo thrashed Goiás 6-1 at the Maracanã. |url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/14-07-2019/flamengo-goias.ghtml |access-date=14 July 2019 |website=globoesporte.com |language=pt |archive-date=5 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191205054951/https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/14-07-2019/flamengo-goias.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 25 August 2019, de Arrascaeta scored with a [[bicycle kick]], after a [[Rafinha (footballer, born 1985)|Rafinha]] cross, in a 3–0 win against [[Ceará Sporting Club|Ceará]] at [[Castelão (Ceará)|Castelão]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 August 2019 |title=Flamengo vence Ceará com gol de bicicleta de Arrascaeta e vira líder |trans-title=Flamengo defeats Ceará with a bicycle kick goal from Arrascaeta and becomes the leader. |url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/ce/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/25-08-2019/ceara-flamengo.ghtml |access-date=22 April 2021 |website=Globoesporte.com |language=pt-BR |archive-date=28 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230128041102/https://globoesporte.globo.com/ce/futebol/brasileirao-serie-a/jogo/25-08-2019/ceara-flamengo.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> With that goal he won the [[2019 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] [[Prêmio Craque do Brasileirão#Most Beautiful Goal|goal of the season]] award and also has been nominated to the [[FIFA Puskás Award]] for the second time in his career.<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 November 2020 |title=Bicicleta de Arrascaeta contra o Ceará é indicada ao Puskás de 2020 |trans-title=Arrascaeta's bicycle kick against Ceará is nominated for the 2020 Puskás Award. |url=https://www.gazetaesportiva.com/times/flamengo/bicicleta-de-arrascaeta-contra-o-ceara-e-indicada-ao-puskas-de-2020/ |access-date=22 April 2021 |website=Gazeta Esportiva |language=pt-BR |archive-date=15 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221015234343/https://www.gazetaesportiva.com/times/flamengo/bicicleta-de-arrascaeta-contra-o-ceara-e-indicada-ao-puskas-de-2020/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|work=FIFA.com|title=Nominees for The Best FIFA Football Awards™ 2020 revealed|url=https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/news/nominees-for-the-best-fifa-football-awardstm-2020-revealed|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125090441/https://www.fifa.com/the-best-fifa-football-awards/news/nominees-for-the-best-fifa-football-awardstm-2020-revealed|url-status=dead|archive-date=25 November 2020|date=25 November 2020|access-date=25 November 2020}}</ref>

On 23 November 2019, de Arrascaeta assisted [[Gabriel Barbosa]] on Flamengo's first goal in the [[2019 Copa Libertadores Final]] against the [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]], that the Flamengo won 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/nov/23/copa-libertadores-flamengo-river-plate-match-report |title=Flamengo win Copa Libertadores with amazing comeback against River Plate |date=23 November 2019 |website=The Guardian}}</ref> Less than 24 hours later, Flamengo became champions of the [[2019 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]], with de Arrascaeta scoring 13 goals and giving 14 assists. On 25 February 2022, de Arrascaeta extended his contract with Flamengo until 31 December 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/flamengo-renova-com-matheus-franca-ate-abril-de-2027.ghtml |title=Flamengo renova com Matheus França até abril de 2027 |website=ge.globo |language=pt-BR |date=25 January 2022 |access-date=25 January 2022 |archive-date=31 January 2022 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20220131232558/https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/flamengo-renova-com-matheus-franca-ate-abril-de-2027.ghtml |url-status=live }}</ref> de Arrascaeta finished the 2022 season in high level, as champion of the [[2022 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores 2022]] and the [[2022 Copa do Brasil|Copa do Brasil 2022]] e being named to [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A Team of the Year]] for the second time in his career and to the [[Bola de Prata (Brazil)|Bola de Prata]] for the third time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://placar.abril.com.br/brasileirao/palmeiras-domina-selecao-do-brasileiro-e-endrick-e-eleito-a-revelacao/|title=Palmeiras domina seleção do Brasileiro e Endrick é eleito a revelação|trans-title=Palmeiras dominate the Brasileiro XI and Endrick is chosen as the breakthrough player|work=Placar - O futebol sem barreiras para você |publisher=[[Placar]]|language=pt-BR|date=10 November 2022|accessdate=16 November 2022|archive-date=16 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221116204401/https://placar.abril.com.br/brasileirao/palmeiras-domina-selecao-do-brasileiro-e-endrick-e-eleito-a-revelacao/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/bola-de-prata/artigo/_/id/11210545/premio-espn-bola-de-prata-sportingbet-palmeiras-faz-historia-domina-time-e-se-despede-de-gustavo-scarpa-com-bola-de-ouro-veja-a-selecao-do-brasileirao-2022|title=Prêmio ESPN Bola de Prata Sportingbet: Palmeiras faz história, domina time e se despede de Gustavo Scarpa com Bola de Ouro; veja a seleção do Brasileirão 2022|trans-title=ESPN Bola de Prata Sportingbet Awards: Palmeiras make history, dominate the team and bid farewell from Gustavo Scarpa with a Bola de Ouro; see the 2022 ''Brasileirão'' XI|publisher=ESPN Brasil|language=pt-BR|date=14 November 2022|accessdate=16 November 2022|archive-date=24 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221124074917/https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/bola-de-prata/artigo/_/id/11210545/premio-espn-bola-de-prata-sportingbet-palmeiras-faz-historia-domina-time-e-se-despede-de-gustavo-scarpa-com-bola-de-ouro-veja-a-selecao-do-brasileirao-2022|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 February 2023, the second leg of the [[2023 Recopa Sudamericana]] was played at the [[Maracanã Stadium]] with a season record attendance of 71,411. Flamengo won 1–0, de Arrascaeta scored the winning goal on the last play of the match on the 96th minute. The score forced [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] which remained scoreless. Ironically de Arrascaeta missed the only penalty kick in the shootout as [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]] won 5–4 and lifted the trophy for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/recopa-sul-americana/jogo/28-02-2023/flamengo-independiente-del-valle.ghtml |title=Del Valle bate o Flamengo nos pênaltis e vence a Recopa Sul-Americana no Maracanã |publisher=ge.globo |language=pt-BR |date=28 February 2023 |access-date=5 March 2023}}</ref> On 22 July, in a 1–1 draw against [[América Futebol Clube (MG)|América Mineiro]], de Arrascaeta became the first foreign player in Flamengo's history to reach 100 [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] matches.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Lara |first=Felipe Ferreira de |date=2014-12-01 |title=Responsabilidade Social Corporativa no Futebol do Brasil: Estudos de Caso com as Equipes do Campeonato Brasileiro Série A. |url=https://doi.org/10.5585/podium.v3i2.49 |journal=Podium Sport, Leisure and Tourism Review |volume=03 |issue=2 |pages=01–11 |doi=10.5585/podium.v3i2.49 |issn=2316-932X}}</ref>

On 17 August 2025, de Arrascaeta reached the historic milestone of 100 assists with the Flamengo jersey. The number 10 gave two assists in the 3–1 victory against [[SC Internacional|Internacional]], at [[Estádio Beira-Rio|Beira-Rio]], in the Série A.

==International career==
[[File:Giorgian de Arrascaeta WC2022.jpg|thumb|160px|Giorgian de Arrascaeta playing for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].]]
After scoring twice for [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay]] as they finished runners-up at the [[2013 FIFA U-20 World Cup]], de Arrascaeta made his debut for the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay senior team]] in a friendly match against [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] in September 2014. He assisted the only goal of the game, scored by [[José Giménez]], in the 1–0 win in [[Goyang]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espnfc.com.au/blog/espn-fc-united-blog/68/post/2142706/tim-vickery-four-up-and-coming-prospects-from-brazil-bolivia-peru-and-uruguay|title=Stakes are high in South American friendlies as players look to impress|date=12 November 2014|work=ESPN|archive-date=26 July 2019|access-date=13 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726094214/http://www.espnfc.com.au/blog/espn-fc-united-blog/68/post/2142706/tim-vickery-four-up-and-coming-prospects-from-brazil-bolivia-peru-and-uruguay|url-status=live}}</ref>

De Arrascaeta was included in Uruguay's squad for the [[2015 Copa América]] by coach [[Óscar Tabárez]]. He was assigned the prestigious number 10 shirt, previously worn by national team legend [[Diego Forlán]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Uruguay confirm Copa América squad numbers as Rolán lands Suárez's No.9 |url=http://www.ca2015.com/en/news/uruguay-confirm-copa-america-squad-numbers-with-rolan-taking-suarezs-no9/1g4mw7am9khxi1dcpc7jxfh8f4 |access-date=9 June 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612033334/http://www.ca2015.com/en/news/uruguay-confirm-copa-america-squad-numbers-with-rolan-taking-suarezs-no9/1g4mw7am9khxi1dcpc7jxfh8f4 |archive-date=12 June 2015}}</ref> On 6 June 2015, de Arrascaeta scored his first senior international goal during a 5–1 pre-tournament friendly win over [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]] in [[Montevideo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-copa-warmups-idUKKBN0ON01520150607|title=Argentina, Uruguay impress in Copa America warmups|date=7 June 2015|work=SBS}}{{dead link|date=September 2024|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> De Arrascaeta made his tournament debut as a 64th-minute substitute as Uruguay defeated [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]] 1–0 in their opening group match on 13 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/33081604|title=Uruguay 1–0 Jamaica|date=13 June 2015|work=BBC|archive-date=17 June 2015|access-date=12 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150617012934/http://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/33081604|url-status=live}}</ref> In May 2018 he was named in Uruguay's provisional 26-man [[Uruguay national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – Final 23-man lists|date=6 April 2018|work=goal.com|archive-date=30 March 2019|access-date=2 March 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330205337/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 10 June 2021, de Arrascaeta was confirmed in the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] [[2021 Copa América]] final squad.<ref>{{cite web |date=10 June 2021 |title=Plantel de Uruguay para la Copa América |trans-title=Uruguay's squad for the Copa América. |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/plantel-de-uruguay-para-la-copa-america/ |access-date=10 June 2021 |publisher=[[Uruguayan Football Association]] |language=es |archive-date=12 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210612015404/https://www.auf.org.uy/plantel-de-uruguay-para-la-copa-america/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=10 June 2021 |title=Números de camisetas del plantel para la Copa América |trans-title=Shirt numbers of the squad for the Copa América. |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/numeros-de-camisetas-del-plantel-para-la-copa-america/ |access-date=10 June 2021 |publisher=Uruguayan Football Association |language=es |archive-date=6 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210706171125/https://www.auf.org.uy/numeros-de-camisetas-del-plantel-para-la-copa-america/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 2 December 2022, de Arrascaeta scored both goals in a 2–0 victory over [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]], in the last match of group stage in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar. This was not enough to qualify Uruguay to the knockout stage as [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] won 2–1 against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], advancing from the group stage on four goals scored in the group stage compared to Uruguay's two.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Ghana 0-2 Uruguay: Giorgian de Arrascaeta scores twice but both nations are knocked out of World Cup in Qatar |work=Eurosport |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/world-cup/2022/fifa-world-cup-2022-in-qatar-live-ghana-v-uruguay-updates_sto9248689/story.shtml |date=2 December 2022}}</ref>

On 31 May 2026, de Arrascaeta was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Arrascaeta is Roman Catholic.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Religioso, fã de Riquelme e apaixonado por pão de queijo: Arrascaeta abre o jogo |trans-title=Religious, Riquelme fan, and passionate about cheese bread: Arrascaeta opens up. |url=https://www.goal.com/br/news/229/brasileir%C3%A3o-s%C3%A9rie-a/2015/10/26/16693532/religioso-f%C3%A3-de-riquelme-e-apaixonado-por-p%C3%A3o-de-queijo |access-date=15 September 2021 |website=Goal.com |language=pt |archive-date=14 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714173521/https://www.goal.com/br/news/229/brasileir%C3%A3o-s%C3%A9rie-a/2015/10/26/16693532/religioso-f%C3%A3-de-riquelme-e-apaixonado-por-p%C3%A3o-de-queijo |url-status=live }}</ref> He is of Basque and Italian descent.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.transfermarketweb.com/?action=read&idsel=191729|title=AS ROMA keen on Giorgian DE ARRASCAETA|access-date=15 June 2018|language=en-GB|archive-date=15 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615111513/http://www.transfermarketweb.com/?action=read&idsel=191729|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Un talento al giorno, Giorgian De Arrascaeta: il nuovo gioiello dell'Uruguay |trans-title=A talent a day, Giorgian De Arrascaeta: the new jewel of Uruguay. |url=https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/il-talento-del-giorno/un-talento-al-giorno-giorgian-de-arrascaeta-il-nuovo-gioiello-dell-uruguay-870851 |access-date=15 June 2018 |archive-date=24 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024205551/https://www.tuttomercatoweb.com/il-talento-del-giorno/un-talento-al-giorno-giorgian-de-arrascaeta-il-nuovo-gioiello-dell-uruguay-870851 |url-status=live }}</ref> In December 2025, his first son was born.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-06 |title=Arrascaeta, do Flamengo, posta foto do nascimento do filho em dia de viagem do Intercontinental |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/2025/12/06/arrascaeta-do-flamengo-posta-foto-do-nascimento-do-filho-em-dia-de-viagem-para-a-copa-intercontinental.ghtml |access-date=2026-04-23 |website=ge |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

